In a statement released a short while ago, Phumeza Nhantsi says her dismissal was based on unfounded allegations in relation to a tender with BNP capital. JOHANNESBURG â€“ South African Airways (SAA)'s former chief financial officer (CFO) Phumeza Nhantsi has lodged a case of unfair dismissal with the Commission for Conciliation, Mediation and Arbitration (CCMA) against the national carrier. In a statement released a short while ago, Nhantsi says her dismissal was based on unfounded allegations in relation to a tender with BNP Capital. An internal disciplinary inquiry found Nhantsi and suspended CEO Musa Zwane guilty of gross financial misconduct, negligence and dishonesty. (Edited by Thapelo Lekabe)